		<text>   Handguns</text>
<box>
<text>Handguns are split into eight different types: Light Pistol, Service Revolver, and Heavy Revolver. Light handguns are pocket handguns, with a small magazine or cylinder size and a small punch, but good for hiding away. Standard and service handguns are service weapons used by various law enforcement agencies, as well as your common thugs, at times. Heavy Handguns are pistols and revolvers chambered in large, wide caliber handguns, carried by few and used by even less.</text>
</box>
		<text>   The Standard, Service, and Heavy Pistols come with two</text>
		<text>   Machine Pistols</text>
<box>
<text>Machine Pistols are split into two different types: Light Machine Light Pistol Ammo, and sport a 25 round magazine. Heavy Machine Pistols use Standard Pistol Ammo, and can take Standard Pistol Magazines as well as their own 32 Round magazines. Machine Pistols lack the stock of SMG, but still have the full auto power.</text>
</box>
		<text>   The Heavy Machine Pistol comes with two magazines.</text>
		<text>   SMGs</text>
<box>
<text>Sub-Machine Guns are split into two different types: Light SMG don&#x27;t pack as much as a punch. Heavy SMGs use Standard Pistol ammo, and are bulkier, but pack more of a punch. Non-automatic/burst versions of these rifles can be purchased for −3 WP cost, and a licensed restriction.</text>
</box>
		<text>   The Heavy SMG comes standard with two magazines and a fixed</text>
		<text>   Shotguns</text>
<box>
<text>Shotguns are split into two different types: Hunting Shotgun and ammunition, the application is vastly different. Hunting shotguns are long barreled, small capacity weapons that are primarily used for hunting game. Tactical Shotguns are used by police officers and other LE agencies, often as a police cruiser gun.</text>
</box>
		<text>   Rifles</text>
<box>
<text>Rifles are split into three different types: Assault Rifles, ammo with Light Sniper Rifles and Light Machine Guns, while Battle Rifles and Hunting rifles share Common ammo with Heavy Sniper Rifles and Heavy Machine Guns.Assault rifles are light and maneuverable and hold more ammo, but fire weaker rounds. Battle rifles are unwieldy, but sturdy and powerful, however holding less ammunition. Hunting rifles boast increased accuracy at the loss of automatic fire.</text>
</box>
		<text>   Machine Guns</text>
<box>
<text>Machine Guns are split into two different types: Light and Rifles and Light Assault Rifles, while Medium Machine Guns share common ammo with Heavy Sniper Rifles, Battle Rifles, and Hunting Rifles. Light Machine Guns are light and maneuverable, but fire weaker rounds and don&#x27;t punch through cover as well. Heavy Machine Guns are unwieldy, but sturdy and powerful, useful for heavy cover.</text>
</box>
		<text>   Sniper Rifles</text>
<box>
<text>Sniper Rifles are split into two different types: Light Sniper ammo with Light Machine Guns and Light Assault Rifles, while Heavy Sniper Rifles share Common ammo with Heavy Machine Guns, Battle Rifles and Hunting Rifles. Both rifles are accurate and do the job well, but one is lighter and easier to carry while one is heavier and packs a bigger punch.</text>
</box>
		<text>   Explosive Launchers</text>
<box>
<text>Explosive Launchers are split into two different types: Grenade but both can be devastating against a group of enemies. Grenade launcher lobs a loaded grenade at a single square. The rocket launcher is a single use rocket, meant to be discarded after each use. Rocket Launchers deal fire and concussion damage.</text>
</box>
